## Solution

This problem can be solved by parsing each equation, and extracting the variable names from the parsed equation. To parse the equation, we can use a regular expression to identify the variables. The regular expression we will use is `r'(?<=[a-zA-Z0-9])\b[a-zA-Z0-9_]+\b(?=[a-zA-Z0-9])'`, which matches a word boundary followed by a variable name.

```python
import re

def extract_variables(equations):
    """Extract all unique variable names from a list of equations.

    Args:
        equations (list): A list of equations.

    Returns:
        list: A list of unique variable names.
    """
    variables = set()
    for equation in equations:
        parsed_equation = re.findall(r'(?<=[a-zA-Z0-9])\b[a-zA-Z0-9_]+\b(?=[a-zA-Z0-9])', equation)
        variables.update(parsed_equation)
    return list(variables)
```

